                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="15180538" author="dosgiuser" created="Fri, 4 Mar 2016 21:08:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Is this still an issue with 4.2.15?  This is a pretty bad issue.  We have a lot of configuration we drop in with fileinstall... then users will go to the webconsole to refine the properties.  As soon as they do that, the config pid is now completely disconnected from the backing file.  The worst part is that if you restart felix/karaf, fileinstall will see the file and reinstall it so now you have 2 separate configurations which breaks a lot of things.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15180614" author="gossmer" created="Fri, 4 Mar 2016 21:55:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;yes, this is still an issue.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15181660" author="cziegeler" created="Sat, 5 Mar 2016 10:02:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think the web console should leave all configuration properties which are not in the metatype description untouched&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15307345" author="cziegeler" created="Tue, 31 May 2016 07:23:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve updated the web console to leave all properties not covered by metatype as-is&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
